
[1]mica

   MI'CA, n. [L. mica, a grain or particle; mico, to shine.] A mineral of
   a foliated structure, consisting of thin flexible lamels or scales,
   having a shining surface. The scales are sometimes parallel, sometimes
   interwoven, sometimes wavy or undulated, sometimes representing
   filaments. It is called also talck, glimmer, muscovy-glass, and glist.

   Jameson subdivides mica into ten subspecies, viz. mica, pinite,
   lepidolite,chlorite, green earth, talck, nacrite, potstone, steatite
   and figure stone.
